Can be written like so (not necessary though, just letting you know):
val folder = BaseItemDto().apply {
	id = ""
	name = activity?.getString(R.string.lbl_recorded_tv)
}
When you want to go all-out this one won't use any variables (Should probably add some new lines to make it readable though):
activity!!.startActivity(Intent(activity, BrowseRecordingsActivity::class.java).apply {
	putExtra("Folder", TvApp.getApplication().serializer.SerializeToString(BaseItemDto().apply {
		id = ""
		name = activity.getString(R.string.lbl_recorded_tv)
	}))
})
Kotlin can do a lot of fun things like this :)
